            ProductSecurity Engineer<br />
<br />
Are youinterested in working on security at one of biggest global internet companies?Be a part of a dynamic team that Yahoo! provides a safe and securityenvironment for all of its users. We are looking for a range of skilledsecurity engineers to help secure new products as they launch and reviewexisting platforms and properties. Candidates should have a strongunderstanding of software development and how to build secure web applicationsat scale.<br />
<br />
Requirements<br />
<br />
- 2 yearsof relevant work experience in the internet security industry<br />
<br />
- must have hands-on experience developing or supporting largescalable web based solutions<br />
<br />
- strong understanding of networking, protocols and how theinternet works<br />
<br />
- strong communication skills<br />
<br />
- solid scripting skills in one of the following:PHP/Perl/Python/Ruby using UNIX<br />
<br />
- familiarity of Unix, OSX, and Windows<br />
<br />
Nice tohave:<br />
<br />
-experience building mobile applications on Android, iOS or Windows tablet<br />
<br />
- BS/MSin Math, Engineering or Computer Science or equivalent of relevant workexperience<br />
<br />
-understanding of database and NoSQL systems<br />
<br />
Responsibilities:<br />
<br />
- performcode reviews to audit and look for security flaws in internal products andthird party solutions including SaaS, PaaS and outsourced or hybrid solutions<br />
<br />
- perform and drive software designs and architectural reviews toensure security is built in<br />
<br />
- interact with product groups, properties and platform technologygroups<br />
<br />
- drive security awareness<br />
<br />
- developdomain expertise and offer guidance company wide<br />
<br />
- mentorothers and set direction for future security posture for security team<br />
<br />
- workwith teams of globally located engineers to drive medium to larger projects<br />
<br />
- identify security risks and develop mitigation plans with theability to formulate and drive possible solutions<br />
<br />
- be willing to learn and expand knowledge base
